  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat until shimmering.",
    "Add beef cubes and brown on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Remove beef from the pot and set aside.",
    "Sauté onion, garlic, carrots, and celery in the same pot until softened, about 7 minutes.",
    "Stir in tomato paste and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Pour in red wine, deglaze, scraping browned bits, and reduce by half, about 3 minutes.",
    "Return beef to the pot, add beef stock, rosemary, smoked paprika, salt, and fresh pepper; bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat, simmer uncovered for 90 minutes until beef is tender and stew thickens.",
    "Stir in chopped dark chocolate until melted and glossy; adjust seasoning and serve hot."
  ],
